SYNOPSIS
========
   int strrstr(string str, string str2         )
   int strrstr(string str, string str2, int pos)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Returns the index of the first occurence of str2(E) in str(E) searching 
   from position pos(E) (default: `-1 == string end`) on backward. In other 
   words: the index of the last occurance of str2(E) before the given position
   pos(E).

   The returned index is relative to the beginning of the string.

   If str2(E) is not found in str(E), -1 is returned.

   If pos(E) is negative, it designates the start position relative to the end
   of the string (the search will still proceed towards the beginning of the 
   string).

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.2.10)

SEE ALSO
========
   strstr(E), strlen(E), sscanf(E), sprintf(E), explode(E)
